sional NMR techniques.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Earnstbio_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Richard_R._Ernst#cite_note-Earnstbio-2\"><span>[<\/span>2<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> These underpin applications of NMR both to <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/NMR_spectroscopy\" title=\"NMR spectroscopy\" class=\"mw-redirect\">chemistry (NMR spectroscopy)<\/a> and to <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Magnetic_resonance_imaging\" title=\"Magnetic resonance imaging\">medicine (MRI)<\/a>. He also received the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Louisa_Gross_Horwitz_Prize\" title=\"Louisa Gross Horwitz Prize\">Louisa Gross Horwitz Prize<\/a> of <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Columbia_University\" title=\"Columbia University\">Columbia University<\/a> in 1991.<\/p>","name":"Richard R. Ernst","place_of_birth":"Winterthur ,  Switzerland","place_of_death":null,"text":"Richard R. Ernst , Chemistry, 1991","year":1991.0}